# Documentation Standards

**README**: Quick start in first 50 lines. Prerequisites, install, run. Link to detailed docs. No implementation details.

**API docs**: Method, path, request/response schema, status codes, errors. Example request/response. Auth requirements. OpenAPI/Swagger for machine-readable.

**Code comments**: Explain why, not what. Document invariants, non-obvious constraints. TODO with ticket ref.

**ADR**: Context (what prompted), Decision (what we chose), Consequences (tradeoffs). One decision per file. `docs/adr/0001-use-postgres.md`.

**Linking & navigation**: Prefer concrete entry docs when available (`README.md`, `SKILLS.md`, `.mdc`) over folder-only links. In tables, do not repeat the same destination in both path and description columns.

**Parser-friendly structure**: Use bullets for independent constraints (`Do not`, `Required`, `Verify`). Prefer explicit table columns for category comparisons (for example, `Primary` vs `Fallback`) instead of mixed cells. Avoid semicolon-chaining unrelated policy constraints in one sentence.
